HEADWORD: Fidia
<hw>Fid"i*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., prob. fr. L.
<ets>fidus</ets> trusty.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of small
beetles, of which one species (the grapevine Fidia, <spn>F.
longipes</spn>) is very injurious to vines in America.</def>⟦br⟧
